{"word":"Baanah","slug":"baanah","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Baanah</b> <a href=\"#/H1196\">H1196</a> <br/> 1. A captain of Ish-Bosheth's army<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=4&verse=2'>2Sa 4:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=4&verse=6'>2Sa 4:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=4&verse=9'>2Sa 4:9</a><br/> 2. Father of Heleb<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=23&verse=29'>2Sa 23:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=30'>1Ch 11:30</a><br/> 3. A chief Jew of the exile<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=2&verse=2'>Ezr 2:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=7&verse=7'>Neh 7:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=10&verse=27'>Neh 10:27</a><br/> 4. The name is spelled Baana, son of Hushai<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=4&verse=16'>1Ki 4:16</a>"}]}